byline.contributor: Amy Chozick reported from Nashua, Patrick Healy from Des Moines, and Yamiche Alcindor from Keene, N.H. Jason Horowitz contributed reporting from Manchester, N.H.
byline.original: By AMY CHOZICK, PATRICK HEALY and YAMICHE ALCINDOR

abstract: Hillary Rodham Clinton and Bernie Sanders intensify their presidential campaigning in New Hampshire ahead of primary, after Clinton's razor-thin victory in Iowa Democratic caucuses; candidates are in unexpected positions.

headline.print_headline: Clinton and Sanders Intensify Efforts in New Hampshire After Iowa Squeaker
headline.main: Hillary Clinton and Bernie Sanders Intensify Efforts in New Hampshire After Iowa Standoff

snippet: Final vote counts showed Mrs. Clinton narrowly beating Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont, according to The Associated Press and other news organizations.
lead_paragraph: Final vote counts showed Mrs. Clinton narrowly beating Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont, according to The Associated Press and other news organizations.
